<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9753084092407></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9753084092407><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=9753084092407>Life as a Tier`dal Assassin</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=9753084092407#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2257><span id= >Kaguk</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>24 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Nov 27th 2:00 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The number one reason to be a Dark Elf Rogue is roleplay.  Stat wise, we don't make exceptional rogues, as our strength is quite low, and once you hit higher levels, you notice that your backstabs are doing MUCH less damage than a rogue of a different race (eg.  28th DE rogue with JCP max backstab at 119 str is the same as my 20th Barb rogue with the same equipment at 183 str)...  And getting good rogue weapons are much more dificult than other melees...  On Fennin, you can pick up D. Dirks (6/22 piercer) for around 60pp, while a comprable warrior weapon, like the langseax (6/23 1h slasher) goes for 10pp.  Unless you twink you probably won't be able to solo past 15, and when I say twink I mean Treeweave/trak tooth etc type twink.  Now for the bonuses...  On the two servers I play on (Fennin and Terris) Tier`dal seem to be much more supportive of others of their race than other races...  When I first started playing the game, a high level rogue noticed I was in trouble and ploped a few items in the trade window and gave me them.  I'm not saying this happens all the time, but I try to return the favor when I can by giving to the newbie community of Tier`dal.  Secondly, we're really not as bad off factionwise as most portray us...  I'll admit I'll never be accepted by the inhabitants of Faydwer as a Dark Elf (killing crushbone orcs lowers the Dark Elf warrior guild), but I was not KoS to the humans in freeport, as well as the ogres or trolls.  Faction was easy to fix in Rivervale (read:  killing goblins) and Qeynos (read:  killing gnolls)...  It didn't take too much effort on either part.  You might not even be KoS in said places if you don't worship Innoruuk as I did, a friend started playing a Dark Elf chanter that was agnostic to try to get a stein of Moggok, and she was not KoS in Rivervale.  For a more indepth look at rogues, I reccomend visiting the Safehouse at <br><br><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse" target=_new>http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse</a> <br><br>-Aenar Velg`arn, 28th Tier`dal Rogue<br> Taludor Magness, 20th Barbarian Rogue<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

