<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97095135930109></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97095135930109><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=97095135930109>RE: Hide-sneak and Evade explained</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=97095135930109#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Oct 7th 4:42 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You have the whole hide-sneak and evade thing all wrong, hide and sneak are to get you past the monster if he has not engaged you yet, if a monster has you on his hate list there is no way to hide from it, it will find you unless 4 things happen 1- you die 2-the monster dies/is killed 3- you zone or 4- an enchanter mezzmerizes it (thereby wiping its hate list).    <br>Now evade is for when you and atleast 1 other person is engaged (on the monsters hate list) the monster decides who is the larger threat you or the other person and attacks who it believes to be a larger threat to its well being.  So if you and a warrior are fighting an orc and you backstab the orc and are doing more damage to him than the warrior then the orc is going to turn and attack you, if the warrior is doing more damage the mob with attack the warrior.  So if the mob is attacking you and you evade (turn off attack and hit hide, then turn attack back on) it will say wether you dodge out of combat (or something to that extent) succeeds or fails, if you fail then nothing happens, if you succeed it makes the mob see you as less of a threat and will turn and attack the warrior or some other person on the mobs hate list.   Of course if the mobs turns around and you backstab it you may push yourself back to the top of the hate list and the mob will attack you again, then just evade again, backstab and repeat just don't let the mob really hate you because rogues can't take those hits that good.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
