<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9695287407608></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9695287407608><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=9695287407608>Followup:</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=9695287407608#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=1250><span id= >Dagis</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>3 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Sep 21st 5:32 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>When killing wisps DON'T sell their Greater Lightstones to a vender. Go ahead and sell the lightstones (Burntout ones you might as well destroy) but keep the greater lightstones, and make a trip to North Karana. In the gypsy camp (grab a map if you need help finding it and haven't been there before, it's right at a crossroads so it shouldn't be too difficult) there's the gypsy Mrysila, give her your Greater lightstones to her one at a time for a Concordance of Research. The Concordance is a combinable container (for pure caster's research) that you can sell back to one of her Gypsy friends for around 7 platinum. (about what I got with 45 charisma as a dwarf) Just check around with the other gypsies, they give different prices, I forget which one is best but it should only take you a minute to figure it out. Two extra things: the Concordance IS a container, so you want to make sure you have an empty inventory slot doing this quest. Also, Mrysila will also take lightstones, but I say don't give them to her because lightstones sell to a vender for about 7 gold, but the item you get back from Mrysila (one of two books) sells for less than a gold.<br><br>This is a great money maker that I wish I knew about when I started my character, I would be much richer for it now.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
