	   <tr><td colspan=2>High agi and dex should be mandatory attributes for successful rogues.  Ive focused and pooled all my money to buy what accessory or armor that would beef up those attributes that people would advertise. I've repeatedly sold my armor and pleaded like a little lady can only could to buy and connive stuff off of people.  Realize that people auction items at what they hope to get it for, not for what they know they only could get. If its 100pp, i shave it down to 80.  Ive gotten 80pp down to 55, when after some pleading he gave in - and truly, thats all i could give him, lol - i usually always just squeak by somehow.  But at 20th level, my agi is 129 and dex of 116.  I come out of combat less hurt than the warriors, even when fighting toe to toe. Most of the time, they miss me, even in an attack combination, or i parry or dodge, lol.  High dex REALLY helps you learn skills quickly!, also helps in bow/throw, and defense.  Lastly, it always help to be a sub-honorable rogue - people really appreciate it. Always help out with people on the brink of death or got trains on them if you can handle it, be very gracious and appreciative and thankful when you get a good deal.  Believe me, it comes around for you.  You dont have to be burning bridges because your a rogue - i believe in being an honorable thief - deal with men justly, deal with monsters unjustly!  <br><br>pp whats the going price on a stilleto of the bloodclaw?  Im planning to go to lavastorm and beg me one.  Ive got a dragoon dirk and a scout's blade right now<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
