	   <tr><td colspan=2>Finding out that you need faction in most all cities, i've created a high charisma character to do my dealings in each city i go to - one way to get what you want and at the best price too!  You just have to find a secret place to swap stuff from character to character.  The rogue is my first character so i've had to invent some strategies to make life simpler.  Another is putting backstab as a hotkey and attacking a mili sec after, creating a combined attack.  Put pickpocket under a hotkey and quickly press your auto-attack button on your keyboard to stop attacking, then press your pickpocket hotkey. Then hit your auto attack keyboard button again - you can pickpocket and attack on humanoids at the same time like how a rogue really suppose to, lol - once you get used to quickly toggling the buttons.  You can max out your pickpocket for your level in a heartbeat at BB.  Best i've stole during combat was a gnollskin off an elite, lol! Ive stole pelts(how does that happen?) and weapons and other goodies during combat also.  In groups, you can pull critters, then unattack and hide and quickly pull away from combat to get back in to backstab when they turn to attack the others.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
